Two days after a 17-year-old shot at a student of Jamia Millia Islamia during a protest against the new citizenship law, a man fired at least two shots about 50 metres from the stage at the Shaheen Bagh protest on Saturday. No one was injured in the firing, which took place around 4.45 pm.

The man, who identified himself as Kapil Gujjar while being taken away by police, was nabbed by volunteers and passers-by. â€œHe has identified himself as Kapil, a 25-year-old resident of Dallupura (East Delhi). A country-made pistol was recovered from his possession and two empty cartridges were found at the spot,â€ said DCP (Southeast) Chinmoy Biswal.

